### Key Classes

| Class | Module | Purpose |
|-------|--------|---------|
| `ENGINE` | `sneeze` | The engine class -- the single entry point Artemis instantiates. Lives in namespace `SNEEZE`. Uses the pimpl idiom (`class Impl; Impl* m_pImpl;`). Constructor takes an `IENGINE*` (host interface). `Initialize()` is parameterless -- reads engine-level configuration from the `IENGINE*` host (`sAppDataPath()`, `sRenderer()`). Uses nested `if` success pattern with `bool m_bInitialized`. Performs nested initialization of engine-level (not per-context) modules: curl_global_init -> WASM_RUNTIME -> SPV_PIPELINE -> XR_RUNTIME (if enabled) -> UI_CONTEXT -> PERSONA -> CONTROL -> InitializePaths. NETWORK and STORAGE are no longer engine-level — they are per-context, owned by CONTEXT. `InitializePaths()` creates the cache directory structure (`sAppDataPath/Sneeze/Cache/Persistent/` and `.../Transitory/`), scans Transitory for orphaned folders (queues them directly into CONTROL for cleanup by AGENT::SCRUB), then creates the current session's transitory folder (`s` + 8 random hex chars). All filesystem operations use `std::error_code` (never throws). Stores `m_sPath_Persistent`, `m_sPath_Transitory` (root), and `m_sPath_Transitory_Session`. Context lifecycle: `Context_Open(pHost, sUrl, kSession)` computes permanent/temporary paths based on session type, creates a CONTEXT, adds it to `m_apContext` (add-before-init), calls Initialize. On failure: removes, queues cleanup, deletes. `Context_Close(pContext)` captures temporary path, deletes pContext (delete-before-erase), erases from `m_apContext`, queues folder for scrub cleanup. `Context_Capture()` / `Context_GetList()` / `Context_Release()` provide thread-safe context iteration (capture/release guards `m_mxContext`). `~Impl()` teardown: closes all lingering contexts, queues the session folder for scrub, deletes subsystems in reverse order. Public API: `Host()`, `Persona()`, `sPath_Persistent()` / `sPath_Session()`, `Context_Open()` / `Context_Close()`, `Queue_Post_Fetch()` / `Queue_Post_Compositor()`, `Login()` / `Logout()` / `ChangePersona()`, `Log()`. Static constants: `sFOLDER_PERSISTENT`, `sFOLDER_TRANSITORY`. Non-copyable, non-movable. Public header: `include/Sneeze.h`. Implementation: `sneeze/Engine.cpp`. |
| `ENGINE::IENGINE` | `sneeze` | Host interface between the application and the engine. Nested inside ENGINE. The host creates a concrete subclass (e.g. Artemis's `ENGINE_HOST`), and implements pure virtual accessors and callbacks. **Pure virtual accessors** (read by engine during Initialize): `sAppDataPath()` (required -- root application data directory, e.g. `%APPDATA%/Metaversal/Persistent`), `sRenderer()` (ANARI library name, e.g. `"halogen"`). **Callbacks** (host must implement): `Log(eLOGLEVEL, sModule, sMessage)` (engine log output). The `I` prefix follows the project's interface naming convention. Initialization pattern: host creates concrete IENGINE, passes it to `ENGINE` constructor, then calls `Initialize()`. The engine reads configuration via the `IENGINE*` accessor methods. |
| `ICONTEXT` | `sneeze` | Per-context host interface for inspector callbacks. The application creates a concrete subclass and passes it to `ENGINE::Context_Open()`. **Optional virtual callbacks** (default no-op): `OnNetworkFileCreated(FILE*)` (returns bool — host-decides pattern), `OnNetworkFileChanged(FILE*)`, `OnNetworkFileDeleted(FILE*)`, `OnStorageSiloCreated(SILO*)`, `OnStorageSiloChanged(SILO*, eSILO_SCOPE, sPath)`, `OnStorageSiloDeleted(SILO*)`, `OnConsoleStreamCreated(STREAM*)`, `OnConsoleStreamDeleted(STREAM*)`, `OnConsoleEntryCreated(shared_ptr<const ENTRY>)`, `OnConsoleEntryDeleted(shared_ptr<const ENTRY>)`. Separated from `IVIEWPORT` so that inspector notifications route through the context (which owns CONSOLE, NETWORK, and STORAGE), not the viewport (which only renders). Public header: `include/Sneeze.h`. |
| `IVIEWPORT` | `sneeze` | Per-viewport host interface for rendering. The application creates a concrete subclass and passes it to `CONTEXT::Viewport_Attach()`. **Pure virtual methods** (host must implement): `FrameWindow()` (returns `void*` platform window handle), `FrameSize(nWidth, nHeight)` (returns current viewport dimensions), `OnFrameReady(pFB, nFbW, nFbH)` (compositor finished a frame for this viewport). Stripped of inspector callbacks (those moved to `ICONTEXT`). Public header: `include/Viewport.h`. |
| `CONTEXT` | `context` | Per-tab session context — the engine-side representation of a browser tab. Analogous to Chrome's BrowsingContext. Constructor takes `ENGINE*` + `ICONTEXT*` + `eSESSION` + `sPath_Permanent` + `sPath_Temporary` (paths computed by ENGINE::Impl::Context_Open). Uses pimpl (`class Impl; Impl* m_pImpl;`). `Initialize(sUrl)` creates and initializes CONSOLE, NETWORK, STORAGE, SCENE, and VIEWPORT in order. `~Impl()` deletes them in reverse. Owns `eSESSION` enum (`kSESSION_PERSISTENT`, `kSESSION_TRANSITORY`). Owns two path strings. `Logout()` calls `NETWORK::Clear()`. Viewport rendering is managed by `VIEWPORT::Activate(IVIEWPORT*)` / `Deactivate()` — Artemis calls these through the CONTEXT's viewport. A CONTEXT always owns a VIEWPORT, but the VIEWPORT only renders when an `IVIEWPORT` host is attached — enabling headless contexts for inactive tabs. Accessors: `Engine()`, `Host()`, `Console()`, `Network()`, `Storage()`, `Scene()`, `Viewport()`, `WasmRuntime()`, `Path_Permanent()`, `Path_Temporary()`. `WasmRuntime()` is a pass-through to `Engine()->WasmRuntime()` — provides symmetry with other subsystem accessors so callers (e.g. CONTAINER) don't reach through the engine. Container lifecycle: `Container_Open(FABRIC* pFabric)` composes a CID from `pFabric->Msf()` (fingerprint, organization, container name, trust level) — or constructs a well-known root CID (`sFingerprint="Sneeze"`, `sContainer="Root"`, `eTrust=kTRUST_ROOT`) when `Msf()` returns null (i.e. FABRIC_ROOT). Finds-or-creates a CONTAINER in `m_umpContainer` (keyed by `CID::Key()`), calls `pContainer->Open(pFabric)`. `Container_Close(FABRIC* pFabric, CONTAINER* pContainer)` calls `pContainer->Close(pFabric)` — container persists at refcount 0 as a lightweight identity shell (not deleted until `~Impl()` iterates `m_umpContainer` and deletes all). The old `CID_Pool` / `m_umCID` mechanism has been eliminated — CONTAINER::Identity() is the single authoritative `const CID*` source. All per-context modules (CONSOLE, STORAGE, NETWORK) receive `const CID*` pointers from CONTAINER directly. Non-copyable, non-movable. Public header: `include/Context.h`. Implementation: `context/Context.cpp`. |
| `VIEWPORT` | `viewport` | Per-viewport instance. Constructor takes `CONTEXT*`. Uses pimpl pattern (`class Impl; Impl* m_pImpl;`). `Renderer_Initialize()` is deferred — called from compositor agent 0 thread (Filament thread affinity) via `Execute_Create`. Creates `RENDERER::ANARI`, sets `m_tpLastFrame`. `Renderer_Shutdown()` is also called from compositor agent 0 via `Execute_Destroy`. `Activate(IVIEWPORT*)` creates a `JOB_COMPOSITOR` for this viewport and posts it to `POOL_CYCLE` via `ENGINE::Queue_Post_Compositor()`. `Deactivate()` calls `JOB_COMPOSITOR::Cancel()` (blocks until renderer is destroyed on agent 0), then deletes the job and nulls the host pointer. `~VIEWPORT()` calls `~Impl()` which calls `Deactivate()`. Owns: RENDERER (as `VIEWPORT::RENDERER`), INPUT (accumulated per-frame mouse/key state), framebuffer (RGBA pixel buffer + mutex), VIEW (camera orbit state), dimensions, JOB_COMPOSITOR* (lifecycle tied to Activate/Deactivate). SCENE ownership moved to CONTEXT — `Scene()` delegates to `Context()->Scene()`. Per-viewport frame timing: `eACCUMULATE` enum (`kACCUMULATE_INPUT`, `kACCUMULATE_SCENE`, `kACCUMULATE_SUBMIT`, `kACCUMULATE_RENDER`, `kACCUMULATE_PUBLISH`), two `Accumulate()` overloads (one takes `steady_clock::time_point` and computes duration to now, one takes pre-computed `double dSeconds`), `Diagnostics()` logs FPS and per-section averages once per second then resets accumulators. `m_tpLastFrame` is set once in `Renderer_Initialize()` and updated at the end of each `Diagnostics()` call. `m_tmNow` (int64_t) for epoch time (not yet wired to advance — celestial animation pending). Public API: `Engine()`, `Context()`, `Host()`, `Scene()`, `IsActive()`, `Renderer()`, `View()`, `Width()`, `Height()`, `SetDimensions()`, `Input_Mouse()`, `Input_Key()`, `Input_Consume()`, `FrameBuffer_Write()`, `FrameBuffer_Capture()`, `FrameBuffer_Release()`, `Accumulate()`, `Diagnostics()`. Public header: `include/Viewport.h`. Implementation: `viewport/Viewport.cpp`. |
| `CONTAINER` | `context` | Runtime manifestation of an MSF file — wraps WASM modules, SPIR-V shaders, storage silos, SOM objects, and map data. Top-level class in `SNEEZE` namespace (defined in `include/Container.h`). Contains nested CID class + `eTRUST` enum. pImpl pattern. Constructor takes `CONTEXT*` + `const CID*` (copies CID by value into Impl). `Open(FABRIC*)` increments refcount; on 0->1 transition creates STREAM via `m_pContext->Console()->Stream_Open(&m_CID)` (stored as `m_pStream`, accessible via `Stream()` public accessor), SILO via `m_pContext->Storage()->Silo_Open(&m_CID)` (+ Attach), and DEP::WASM_STORE via `m_pContext->WasmRuntime()->Store_Open()` (+ SetHostData to `m_pContext` + InitializeLinker with 32 host functions). `Close(FABRIC*)` decrements; on 1->0 transition tears down in reverse: WasmRuntime()->Store_Close, Silo Detach + Silo_Close, Stream_Close (nulls `m_pStream`). `m_apFabric` is `vector<FABRIC*>` tracking which fabrics hold this container open. Containers persist in `CONTEXT::Impl::m_umpContainer` at refcount 0 as lightweight identity shells — not deleted until CONTEXT destruction. `Identity()` returns `const CID*` (pointer to the Impl's authoritative CID — pointer identity matters, multiple consumers must compare pointers not values). `Key()` returns `const std::string&` (pre-computed map key). `~Impl()` logs via `Engine()->Log()` if destroyed with nonzero refcount, deletes all owned MAP_OBJECTs from `m_apMap_Object`. **Scene Node Handle Table:** CONTAINER owns the authoritative handle-to-NODE mapping for all nodes created by its WASM modules. Two handle maps: `m_umpNode` (`unordered_map<uint64_t, NODE*>`, keyed by `twObjectIx`) and `m_umpFabric` (`unordered_map<uint64_t, FABRIC*>`, keyed by `twFabricIx`). Monotonic counters `m_twObjectIx_Next` and `m_twFabricIx_Next` for auto-assignment. **Critical design decision:** `m_umpNode` is an `unordered_map`, NOT a `vector` — object indices are 48-bit values (range 1 to 2^48-4) and may be sparse. A `vector` would attempt to allocate physical memory for all entries between 0 and the max index. Constants: `OBJECTIX_NULL` (0), `OBJECTIX_IDENTITY` (0xFFFFFFFFFFFF — auto-assign sentinel), `OBJECTIX_MAX` (0xFFFFFFFFFFFB), `OBJECTIX_ERROR` (0xFFFFFFFFFFFC). `FABRICIX_*` parallels. Public API: `Node_Root(twFabricIx, pRMCObject)` — creates root node for a fabric (guards: `pRMCObject != null`, fabric exists, no existing root). `Node_Open(twParentIx, pRMCObject)` — creates child node (guards: parent exists in handle table). `Node_Close(twObjectIx)` — removes node from handle table, deletes NODE + MAP_OBJECT. `Node_Find(twObjectIx)` — lookup by handle. `Instance_Open(twFabricIx, sUrl, sHash, aWasmBytes)` — compiles + instantiates WASM module. `Instance_Close(twFabricIx, sUrl, sHash)` — tears down instance. Mutex: `m_mxContainer` (recursive_mutex) guards all public entry points (`Node_Root`, `Node_Open`, `Node_Close`). `Node_Create` is internal-only (called inside the lock). `Node_Create` constructs a `MAP_OBJECT_CELESTIAL`, copies RMCOBJECT wire-format fields (name as wide-to-narrow char conversion, celestial type, position, scale, bound, radius, mass, orbit), creates NODE, calls Initialize, stores in both `m_umpNode` and `m_apMap_Object`. RMCOBJECT is a 432-byte packed C struct (`#pragma pack(push, 1)`, `static_assert(sizeof == 432)`) defined in `src/context/scene/MapObject.h` — the wire format for WASM-to-C++ scene object transfer. Contains sub-structs: OBJECT_HEAD (with TWORD Self containing 48-bit ObjectIx), MAP_OBJECT_NAME (48 wchar_t), MAP_OBJECT_TYPE, MAP_OBJECT_OWNER, MAP_OBJECT_RESOURCE, MAP_OBJECT_TRANSFORM, MAP_OBJECT_ORBIT, MAP_OBJECT_BOUND, MAP_OBJECT_PROPERTIES. TWORD is a 6-byte packed struct with `ObjectIx()` accessor that masks the top 2 bytes. Impl members: `m_pContainer`, `m_pContext`, `m_CID` (by value), `m_sKey`, `m_nCount_Open`, `m_mxContainer` (recursive_mutex), `m_pStream` (CONSOLE::STREAM*), `m_pSilo` (STORAGE::SILO*), `m_pWasm_Store` (DEP::WASM_STORE*), `m_twObjectIx_Next`, `m_umpNode` (unordered_map<uint64_t, NODE*>), `m_apMap_Object` (vector<MAP_OBJECT*>), `m_twFabricIx_Next`, `m_umpFabric` (unordered_map<uint64_t, FABRIC*>). |
| `CONTAINER::CID` | `context` | Identity record for a container. Fields: `sFingerprint` (SHA-256 of cert public key, 64 hex chars), `sOrganization` (O field from leaf cert), `sOrganizationHash` (truncated SHA-256 of cert subject, 12 hex chars), `sContainer` (from MSF payload), `sPersonaHash`, `eTrust` (eTRUST enum). Default constructor initializes `eTrust` to `kTRUST_NONE`. `eTRUST` has 6 levels: `kTRUST_NONE` (black), `kTRUST_UNTRUSTED` (red), `kTRUST_UNVERIFIED` (orange), `kTRUST_EXPIRED` (yellow), `kTRUST_VERIFIED` (green), `kTRUST_ROOT` (browser root fabric — used by FABRIC_ROOT's synthetic CID). `DisplayName()` returns `sOrganization + "/" + sContainer` for trusted/expired (yellow/green), `sOrganizationHash + "/" + sContainer` for untrusted (red/orange/black). `Key()` returns the map key string used by `m_umpContainer`. FILE stores `CID m_CID` by value (copied from `const CID*` passed to `File_Open`). SILO stores CID by value (`CID m_CID`, copied from the raw `const CID*` passed to `Silo_Open`). |
