| `POOL_QUEUE<JOB_PTR>` | `sneeze/control` | Template subclass of POOL. Typed, thread-safe job queue. `Post(pJob)` appends under `m_mxQueue`, CAS-claims first idle agent (`Busy()`), signals it. `Grab(pJob)` pops front; false on empty. Explicit instantiations for `JOB_FETCH*` and `JOB_SCRUB*` in `Pool_Queue.cpp`. |
| `POOL_CYCLE` | `sneeze/control` | Perpetual job pool for compositor jobs (`Pool_Cycle.cpp`). Subclass of POOL. Jobs remain in the pool until explicitly `Remove()`'d (unlike POOL_QUEUE where jobs are consumed). `Post(pJob)` appends and signals first idle agent. `Grab(pJob, nAgentIz)` selects the best available job: Create/Destroy states are routed exclusively to agent 0 (Filament thread affinity); Ready/Present states round-robin by `m_nLastFrame` (longest-ago-rendered gets priority). Each candidate job is test-locked via `Busy()` (acquires `m_mxJob`); losers are released via `Idle()`; the winner is unlocked via `Unlock()`. `Remove(pJob)` erases a job from the pool (called by `Execute_Destroy` after renderer shutdown). Protected by `m_mxCycle` (std::mutex). |
| `JOB_COMPOSITOR` | `sneeze/control` | Perpetual viewport rendering job (`Compositor.cpp`). Inherits IJOB. Constructor takes `VIEWPORT*`. State machine: `kSTATE_CREATE` -> `kSTATE_RENDER` -> `kSTATE_PRESENT` (loop) -> `kSTATE_DESTROY`. `m_bBusy` (non-atomic bool, guarded by `m_mxJob` std::mutex) — `Busy()` test-and-set acquires the mutex, `Idle()` clears and releases, `Unlock()` releases without clearing. `Return(eState)` acquires `m_mxJob`, updates state (unless already kSTATE_DESTROY), clears busy, releases — called by Execute_* methods to return the job to the pool. `Cancel()` acquires `m_mxCancel` (recursive_mutex), sets state to kSTATE_DESTROY under `m_mxJob`, then blocks on `m_cvCancel.wait()` until `m_bCancelled` is true. `Complete()` sets `m_bCancelled = true` under `m_mxCancel` and signals `m_cvCancel`. The mutex is NOT held during Execute calls — Cancel can proceed between Grab cycles without starvation. `m_nLastFrame` (int64_t) tracks the global frame sequence number for round-robin scheduling. Created by `VIEWPORT::Impl::Activate()`, posted to `POOL_CYCLE` via `ENGINE::Queue_Post_Compositor()`. Destroyed by `VIEWPORT::Impl::Deactivate()` after `Cancel()` returns. |
| `AGENT` | `sneeze/control` | Abstract base class for engine agent threads. Inherits `THREAD`. Constructor takes `(POOL* pPool, int nAgentIz)`. `Engine()` accessor delegates to `m_pPool->Engine()` — agents follow the ownership chain (AGENT -> POOL -> CONTROL -> ENGINE). `Busy()` — CAS on `m_bBusy` (atomic): `POOL_QUEUE::Post` calls this to claim an idle agent. `Main()` is pure virtual. Queue-driven agents use `Wait([this] { return Job(); })` where `Job()` loops: Grab, process, Release, return `IsShutdown()`. Self-paced agents use their own loop. `~AGENT()` calls `Join()`. Members: `m_pPool` (POOL*), `m_nAgentIz` (int), `m_bBusy` (atomic<bool>). File: `Agent.cpp`. |
