| `MSF` | `context/msf` | Top-level class in `SNEEZE` namespace (un-nested from the former `VIEWPORT::MSF`). Public header: `include/Msf.h`. Single class for the full MSF file lifecycle: parse, sign, verify signature, verify chain, manage certificates, and access typed payload fields. `Parse()` accepts both JWS compact serialization (signed) and plain JSON (unsigned) — heuristic detection based on dot-count and whitespace. For signed JWS: decodes header/payload/signature, extracts cert chain from `x5c`, populates `m_sOrganization` (O field from leaf cert), computes `m_sOrganizationHash` via `CHAIN::HashString`. For plain JSON: parses payload directly, sets trust to `kTRUST_UNTRUSTED`. `VerifySignature()` and `VerifyChain()` are explicit follow-up calls. `IsChainExpired()` detects expired-but-otherwise-valid chains (yellow trust). Payload accessors: `SetContainer()` / `Container()`, `AddService()` / `Services()`, `AddModule()` / `Modules()`. The old `SetNamespace()` / `Namespace()` / `SetOrganization()` / `Organization()` payload accessors have been removed — organization comes from the certificate, not the payload. Display helpers: `Organization()` (from cert O field), `OrganizationHash()`, `DisplayOrganization()` (picks org vs hash based on trust level). Composition path: `SetPayload()` / typed setters + `AddCert()` + `Sign()`. Supports RS256/384/512, ES256/384/512. Non-copyable, non-movable. Implementation: `context/msf/MsfFile.cpp`. |
| `MSF::CHAIN` | `context/msf` | X.509 chain validation via BoringSSL's `X509_STORE`. Nested inside MSF. Loads the Windows ROOT certificate store on Windows (`CertOpenSystemStoreA` + `CertEnumCertificatesInStore`), `X509_STORE_set_default_paths()` on Linux/macOS. Computes the leaf certificate's **public-key fingerprint** — `SHA-256(i2d_PUBKEY(leaf))` — which is the organizational identity used across the browser, the signing tool, and the HTML viewer. `ExtractCertInfo` populates `MSF::CERT` including the `sOrganization` field (O from X.509 subject). `HashString(sInput)` computes truncated SHA-256 (12 hex chars) — used for `sOrganizationHash`. Also exposes 5 public static utility methods (`DecodeInfoDerBase64`, `DecodeInfoPem`, `ComputeFingerprint`, `ExtractPublicKeyPem`, `PemToDerBase64`) that encapsulate all BoringSSL-dependent certificate operations, so `MSF` has no direct BoringSSL dependency. File: `context/msf/Chain.cpp` (renamed from `CertChain.cpp`). |
| `MSF::SERVICE` | `context/msf` | Struct: `sName`, `sType`, `sEndpoint`, `aModuleKeys`. Describes a service within an MSF payload. |
| `MSF::MODULE` | `context/msf` | Struct: `sUrl`, `sHash` (SRI format, e.g. `sha256-hexdigest`). Describes a WASM/SPIR-V module referenced by an MSF payload. |
| `MSF::CERT` | `context/msf` | Struct: `sSubject`, `sIssuer`, `sSerial`, `sNotBefore`, `sNotAfter`, `bIsCA`, `sOrganization` (O field from X.509 subject, populated by `CHAIN::ExtractCertInfo`). Parsed certificate metadata returned by `MSF::CertInfos()`. |

**Naming note:** The concrete renderer class is `renderer::ANARI_RENDERER`. The ANARI SDK's `ANARI_*` enum constants (e.g. `ANARI_RENDERER`, `ANARI_CAMERA`) live in the global namespace, so scoping ours inside `renderer` avoids collision without needing a backend-specific class name.

